cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - family-names: Rawson
    given-names: Douglas
    email: rawson.douglas@gmail.com
title: "Compiled Injection: Deterministic Activation Engineering for Pretrained LLMs"
url: "https://github.com/DRawson5570/compiled-injection"
date-released: 2026-05-16
abstract: >
  A suite of gradient-free techniques for surgically editing the behavior of
  pretrained large language models by directly manipulating activations in the
  residual stream. Includes per-step token injection (solving the
  compound-probability collapse), composed attention+FFN injection, and a
  systematic concept compilation pipeline via pseudo-inverse + SVD.
keywords:
  - mechanistic interpretability
  - activation engineering
  - AI alignment
  - model editing
  - gradient-free optimization
  - transformer circuits
  - language models
license: CC-BY-4.0
